Reclaim Your City 544 | Flits (Amsterdam)  

Hailing from the Netherlands, Flits has made a name for himself over the last couple of years thanks to a series of hard-boiled, uptempo-paced records that bridge the gap between straight out industrial grooves and Birmingham-style traction. True to the powerhouse approach that’s come to define his releases for Molekül, Antidote and his own eponymous platform, Flits steps in the series with a two-hour orgy of mechanistic brutality and sweeping step moves ready to buckle all knees in the vicinity. A no-miss for all lovers of heavy-duty tech business, blast this one out accordingly. Loud and heavy.

track.description:
https://soundcloud.com/saveyouratollofficial
https://www.beatport.com/artist/save-your-atoll/960403

Next up is someone that has really impressed us. Techno has become a less common on this channel but this is one artist we needed to showcase. 

From Turin to Rome then Berlin, from Drum and bass to Dubstep then Ambient, Dubtechno and other musical nuances, this is the background of Save your Atoll (real name Antonello Meloni) through the years.

In the middle, the ring that united everything, the island of Sardinia.
In 2012 he creates with other friends the Roman collective then moved to Berlin, called "Spacedrome".

With this project the first works released on different independent labels (Abyssal audio, Elastica records, Modulate rec., YinYang, Whoyostro, Deep Electronics,Lounge Squatt,Truth or consequence, O’clock rec etc.) are realized. Also in that year he won the contest "unsigned contest" for Knowledge Magazine UK with the song "Mimetic Wormhall". The following year, with Spacedrome, he took part in the Croatian "Outlook festival". He also performs in many clubs in the capital and in other Italian cities as well as some adventure in Europe.

After moving to Berlin the collective has been able to perform in different contexts, from Berlin clubs (Hoppettosse, Acud macht neu, Mensch meyer,About Blank,Void etc.) to festivals (Freqs
of nature,Pik nick electronik etc.).

But you know, artistic paths can lead to changes in perspective and the Spacedrome project is temporarily put aside.
From this break was born Save Your Atoll.
track.title: #274 - Save Your Atoll - (ITA)

track.description:
Art Bei Ton Podcast 081: Feral
( @feral_music )

For the 5th birthday of Art Bei Ton we're happy to celebrate with a special podcast from a special artist and friend, the Italian DJ and Producer Feral.

Mostly known for his rich and hypnotic live sets, he recorded for us a very deep and subtle DJ mix, showing a vast musical knowledge and an extreme quality in the mixing. With many percussive elements, and a vast array of soundscapes, this mix stands out for its clean sound and complex grooves organized in a smooth arrangement. 

Enjoy!

More info about Feral:

Marked by his awakened sensibility to depth, Feral consistently carries a thread of spirituality throughout his work.  He has inherently embodied the spirit of deep techno, of which defines Hypnus Records, through his passion for audio engineering, hardware experimentation and fascination for percussive instruments.

Feral’s affinity for the shamanic calls of the tribal drum have led him across the world to discover and nurture his defining sound. Finding comfort in the solitude of his studio, Feral’s visions emerge in the crepuscular hours of his native city, Rome.  With a heightened sense of spatial awareness, the sounds of Feral unearth the path of his multidimensional world, transporting the listener to a haunting, yet grounding refuge within.

SC: @feral_music
FB: https://www.facebook.com/thisisferal
IG: https://www.instagram.com/feral.heruka/
RA: https://ra.co/dj/feral-it
track.title: Art Bei Ton Podcast 081: Feral

track.description:
Reclaim Your City 529 | Yanamaste (Tbilisi)

An increasingly potent driving force in today’s techno environment, Georgia has through its key clubs Bassiani, Khidi and Mtkvarze, helped Tbilisi and its surroundings shape into of the most intriguing and reliable hotspots for emerging DJs and producers. One of its most talented heralds and a surefire groove rider at that, Yanamaste graces us with a choice two hours of the entrancingly deep and bumpy 4x4 epics he’s been laying down for INNSIGNN, Lyree and Khidi in recent times. Paced-up and animal to the core, his vision sweeps an extra wide range of shades and reliefs, nimbly moving the cursor from classic Berlin-inspired blends to full-fledged magmatic trance, via Birmingham-style projections and a solid dose of folk-infused harmonics. Raw yet technical, organic with a hint of hypermodern hoodoo to it, Yanamaste’s sound is the definition of hardware techno with soul, cut to ram-raid and elevate in equal measure.
